      {
        "subtopic": "English Overview",
        "content": "• India is known as the land of festivals due to its cultural diversity.\n• Every state has its own unique festivals based on religion, agriculture, and seasons.\n• Festivals in India are celebrated with rituals, music, dance, food, and social gatherings.\n• Some festivals are local, while others like Diwali, Holi, and Eid are celebrated nationwide.\n• Seasonal festivals mark harvests and changes in weather, reflecting India’s agricultural roots."
