    "topic": "Andhra Pradesh",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Important Festivals of Andhra Pradesh",
        "content": "• Pongal – A major harvest festival dedicated to the Sun God, celebrated with traditional dishes and rituals.\n\n• Dussehra – Celebrates the victory of Goddess Durga over Mahishasura, marked by grand processions and fairs.\n\n• Ugadi – Telugu New Year festival, celebrated with prayers, Panchanga Sravanam, and festive meals.\n\n• Deccan Festival – Showcases Hyderabad’s arts, crafts, dance, and music traditions.\n\n• Brahmotsavam – A famous religious festival at Tirupati Balaji Temple with grand rituals and processions.\n\n• Visakha Utsav – Cultural festival of Visakhapatnam featuring music, dance, and exhibitions.\n\n• Lumbini Festival – Celebrates the heritage of Buddhism in Andhra Pradesh.\n\n• Rayalaseema Food and Dance Festival – Promotes local cuisines and folk dances of the Rayalaseema region."
      }
