    "topic": "Arunachal Pradesh",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Important Festivals of Arunachal Pradesh",
        "content": "• Reh – Celebrated by the Idu Mishmi tribe to honor the divine mother for prosperity.\n\n• Boori Boot – A fertility festival of the Hill-Miri tribe, seeking blessings for good harvests.\n\n• Myoko – Festival of the Apatani tribe involving rituals for prosperity and protection.\n\n• Dree – Major agricultural festival of the Apatani tribe, praying for bumper crops.\n\n• Pongtu – Harvest festival of the Tutsa tribe with traditional dance and rituals.\n\n• Losar – Tibetan New Year, celebrated with prayers, dances, and cultural performances.\n\n• Murung – A communal festival of the Apatani tribe to ensure prosperity and good health.\n\n• Solung – Agricultural festival of the Adi tribe, thanking deities for harvest and welfare.\n\n• Mopin – Popular festival of the Galo tribe, celebrated with Popir dance for prosperity.\n\n• Monpa Festival – Includes Losar and other local rituals of the Monpa community."
